# Messages Package

This package provides message and attachment handling for the Claude Code harness.

## Skill Listing Mechanism

The Skill Listing mechanism is responsible for informing the LLM about available skills through `<system-reminder>` messages, matching the TypeScript implementation.

### Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     Skill Listing Flow                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

1. Session Start
   ├─> SkillListingManager.GetSkillListingAttachment()
   ├─> Formats all user-invocable skills within budget
   ├─> Returns SkillListingAttachment (isInitial: true)
   └─> Converts to <system-reminder> message

2. Dynamic Discovery (when new skills are found)
   ├─> SkillListingManager.GetSkillListingAttachment()
   ├─> Formats only NEW skills (incremental)
   ├─> Returns SkillListingAttachment (isInitial: false)
   └─> Converts to <system-reminder> message

3. Session Resume
   ├─> SkillListingManager.SuppressNext()
   └─> Marks all skills as sent (avoids duplication)
```

### Components

#### 1. Attachment Types

```go
// SkillListingAttachment represents a skill listing
type SkillListingAttachment struct {
    Content    string // Formatted skill list
    SkillCount int    // Number of skills in this batch
    IsInitial  bool   // true for first batch, false for incremental
}

// Converts to system-reminder format
func (a *SkillListingAttachment) ToSystemReminder() string
```

#### 2. SkillListingManager

Manages incremental skill listing with deduplication:

```go
manager := messages.NewSkillListingManager()

// Get attachment for new skills
attachment := manager.GetSkillListingAttachment(
    allSkills,
    contextWindowTokens, // e.g., 200000
)

if attachment != nil {
    // Inject into conversation as system-reminder
    systemReminder := attachment.ToSystemReminder()
}
```

#### 3. Formatting Logic

**Budget Control:**
- Default: 1% of context window (8000 chars for 200k tokens)
- Bundled skills: Always get full descriptions
- Other skills: Truncated if needed to fit budget

**Description Truncation:**
- Max 250 characters per skill description
- Bundled skills never truncated
- Non-bundled skills truncated proportionally

**Format:**
```
- skill-name: Description text (max 250 chars)
```

### Usage Example

```go
package main

import (
    "github.com/ding/claude-code/claude-go/internal/harness/messages"
    "github.com/ding/claude-code/claude-go/internal/harness/skills"
)

func main() {
    // Create manager
    manager := messages.NewSkillListingManager()
    
    // Get all user-invocable skills
    skillManager := skills.NewSkillManager()
    allSkills := skillManager.ListUserInvocableSkills()
    
    // Initial listing (session start)
    attachment := manager.GetSkillListingAttachment(allSkills, 200000)
    if attachment != nil {
        // attachment.IsInitial == true
        // attachment.SkillCount == len(allSkills)
        systemReminder := attachment.ToSystemReminder()
        // Inject systemReminder into conversation
    }
    
    // Later: dynamic skill discovery
    newSkills := discoverNewSkills()
    allSkills = append(allSkills, newSkills...)
    
    attachment = manager.GetSkillListingAttachment(allSkills, 200000)
    if attachment != nil {
        // attachment.IsInitial == false
        // attachment.SkillCount == len(newSkills) (only new ones)
        systemReminder := attachment.ToSystemReminder()
        // Inject systemReminder into conversation
    }
    
    // Session resume: suppress duplicate listing
    manager.SuppressNext(allSkills)
}
```

### Integration with Engine

The engine should:

1. **Session Start:**
   - Create SkillListingManager
   - Get initial skill listing attachment
   - Inject as system-reminder message

2. **Dynamic Discovery:**
   - When new skills are discovered (e.g., conditional activation)
   - Get incremental skill listing attachment
   - Inject as system-reminder message

3. **Session Resume:**
   - Call SuppressNext() to avoid re-announcing existing skills

### Output Format

```xml
<system-reminder>
The following skills are available for use with the Skill tool:

- commit: Create a git commit with a descriptive message
- review-pr: Review a pull request and provide feedback
- test: Run tests for the project
</system-reminder>
```

### Differences from Old Implementation

| Old (collector.go) | New (messages package) |
|-------------------|------------------------|
| Static in system prompt | Dynamic via system-reminder |
| All skills every time | Incremental updates |
| No budget control | 1% context window budget |
| No deduplication | Tracks sent skills |
| Bundled in context | Separate attachment mechanism |

### TypeScript Parity

This implementation matches the TypeScript version:

- ✅ Attachment-based injection
- ✅ Incremental updates (only new skills)
- ✅ Budget control (1% of context window)
- ✅ Bundled skill priority (never truncated)
- ✅ Description truncation (250 char max)
- ✅ System-reminder format
- ✅ Session resume suppression

### Next Steps

To complete the integration:

1. Update engine to use SkillListingManager
2. Inject skill listing attachments at appropriate times
3. Handle dynamic skill discovery events
4. Implement session resume logic
